            <td width="4" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" class="page-title">&nbsp;</td>
            <td colspan="2" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><div align="center"><span class="caption1 style18"><strong><i> 
                <span class="style24">Web Site Design Competition</span><br>
                </i></strong></span></div>
              <hr align="center" size="0" color="#000000"> <div align="center"></div></td>
            <td width="10" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr> 
            <td height="21">&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td width="140">&nbsp;</td>
            <td width="599"> <p class="caption1 style18"><strong><i>The Winner of the design competition is:</i></strong></p>
            <p class="style18 caption1"><a href="http://www.embolden.com"><font color="#000066">Anne-Marie Harrington, Owner of Embolden Design</font></a></p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="Embolden_Design.html" class="style18 caption1"><font color="#000066">See the Winning Design</font></a> <br>
                </li>
            </ul>        
			<p class="caption1 style18"><strong><i>The Second Place design was submitted by:</i></strong></p>
            <p class="style18 caption1"><font color="#000066">Dan Chapman and Joe Alba</font> </p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="providence" class="style18 caption1"><font color="#000066">See the Second Place Design</font></a> <br>
              </li>
            </ul>     
            <p class="style18 caption1">We would like to thank all the other participants who worked so hard on this competition. Thank you! </p>
         <p class="style18 caption1">&nbsp;</p></td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
      </tr>
          <tr> 
            <td height="43">&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top" class="style12">&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top"><p class="style20"><span class="caption1 style18"><strong><i><span class="style26">Challenge from Mayor Cicilline<br>
            </span></i></strong></span><br>
  The City of Providence is gaining international notoriety for its artists, designers, and creative spirit. As our virtual face to the world, our city&rsquo;s website should live up to that reputation. That&rsquo;s why I&rsquo;m calling on all Providence web design firms, individual designers, and IT professionals who live, work, or study here to compete in a citywide contest to redesign our website, www.providenceri.com, and our e-newsletter, City News. </p>
              <p class="style20">This is your chance to make an important and lasting contribution to our great city and to put your talent on display for a local, national, and international audience. Good luck! </p>
              <p><span class="style22">Mayor David N. Cicilline</span><br>
                <br>
              </p>
            </td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
		  <tr height="5" > 
            <td ></td>
            <td></td>
            <td class="style12">&nbsp;</td>
            <td></td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td >&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top" class="style12"><span class="style16">Entries:
            <!-- <input type="Text" name="approved1" size="10" value=""> -->
            </span></td>
            <td valign="top"><p class="style20">Entries should include the following three redesigned, web-ready pages:</p>
              <ol>
                <li class="style20">Home page</li>
                <li class="style20">City Government page</li>
                <li class="style20">City News e-newsletter (example at providenceri.com/citynews)</li>
              </ol>
              <p class="style20">Entries are due August 31st. Finalists&rsquo; work will be posted to the website and a winner will be determined by September 12 th. </p>
              <p class="style20">Entries should include a CD with web pages and a signed entry form (see below), and be mailed or delivered to Web Design Contest c/o Communications and Press, Office of Mayor David N. Cicilline, 25 Dorrance St. Providence , RI 02903. Entries may also be emailed to <a href="mailto:designcontest@providenceri.com"><font color="#000066">designcontest@providenceri.com</font></a> or posted online, as long as a signed entry form is also mailed or delivered to the above address. </p>
              <BR>
            </td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr height="5" > 
            <td ></td>
            <td></td>
            <td class="style12">&nbsp;</td>
            <td></td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr> 
            <td height="32">&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top" class="style12"><span class="style16">Winning Entry: </span></td>
            <td valign="top"><ul>
              <li class="style20">The winning designer will be part of a press announcement on or after September 8 th.</li>
              <li class="style20">The winning designer will also receive a &ldquo;design by&hellip;&rdquo; credit at the bottom of every page where the design is used.</li>
              <li class="style20">Unfortunately, the City is unable to provide a monetary award to the winning designer.</li>
            </ul></td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
		            <tr height="5" > 
            <td ></td>
            <td></td>
            <td class="style12">&nbsp;</td>
            <td></td>
            <td></td>
          </tr>
          <tr> 
            <td  >&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top" class="style12"><span class="style16">Design Statement:</span></td>
            <td valign="top">
              <p class="style20"><em>Providenceri.com</em> and <em>City News</em> are tools for self-serve government and for accessing the latest City information. They are used by residents of and visitors to Providence -- a cosmopolitan, cultural &ldquo;mecca&rdquo; built on the strength of 25 vibrant and distinctive neighborhoods.<br>
			</p>
            </td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>

		  
