            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top"><span class="style12"><span class="style16">Judging:</span></span></td>
            <td valign="top"><p class="style20">Designs will be judged on: 1) organization of information; 2) visual appeal; 3) readiness for implementation; and 4) interpretation of design statement. </p>
              <p class="style20">A committee including the Director of the Department of Arts, Culture and Tourism; the Press Secretary, the Mayor&rsquo;s Communications Director; the City Webmaster; and the Director of Community Relations will select finalists. Mayor Cicilline will select the final design.</p>
            </td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr> 
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top"><span class="style12"><span class="style16">Suggested Elements: </span></span></td>
            <td valign="top"><p class="style20">Home Page:</p>
              <ul>
                <li class="style20">Site navigation</li>
                <li class="style20">Welcome from Mayor Cicilline</li>
                <li class="style20">Quick access to self-serve government tools</li>
                <li class="style20">Recent news</li>
                <li class="style20">Designated area for new site features/emergency notices</li>
                <li class="style20">Sign-up for City News</li>
              </ul>
         
              <p class="style20">City Government Page (will be replicated as template for other pages):</p>
              <ul>
                <li class="style20">Site navigation</li>
                <li class="style20">Links to City Departments</li>
                <li class="style20">Designated area for important, time-sensitive postings</li>
              </ul>
            
              <p class="style20">City News:</p>
              <ul>
                <li class="style20">Flexible enough to include up to six stories</li>
                <li class="style20">Protocol for managing stories with photographs and those without</li>
                <li class="style20">Designated area for meeting postings</li>
            </ul></td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
