            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
            <td valign="top"><span class="style12"><span class="style16">Design Implementation: </span></span></td>
            <td valign="top"><p class="style20">It is assumed that the winning design will require some degree of modification upon implementation. This could be due to the need to accommodate City and user technology or changes in content requirements. The City will make every effort to maintain the integrity of the design upon implementation. In the unfortunate circumstance that the winner believes the design has been too compromised during implementation, credit may be removed upon request.</p>
            
              <p class="style20">Flexibility of City Government page design:</p>

              <p class="style20">The design for the City Government page in the winning submission will also serve as the basis of a design for a template for all other pages. A design that could allow for a variety of content is encouraged.</p>
            
              <p class="style20">Programming notes:</p>
           
              <p class="style20">The redesigned City Website will be built out using style sheets (CSS) and PHP to serve up all content dynamically from a database. Use of CSS in your submission is encouraged but not required. </p>
           
              <p class="style20">User technical information:</p>
              
              <p class="style20">A wide variety of operating systems and browsers are used to visit providenceri.com and view City News, and the site will continue to meet W3C guidelines (www.w3c.org). Compliance with W3C guidelines in submissions is strongly encouraged.</p>
            
            <p class="style20">Providenceri.com will be fully available to people with disabilities and therefore will be compliant with section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act. Compliance with section 508 (<a href="http://www.section508.com/"><font color="blue">www.section508.com</font></a>) in submissions is encouraged but not required. </p></td>
            <td>&nbsp;</td>
          </tr>
